24:30.094 --> 24:31.929
Great.
So what's next?

24:32.805 --> 24:34.098
Actually, I'd love a cup of coffee.

24:34.182 --> 24:35.516
Okay, I'll run down to the cafeteria.

24:35.600 --> 24:37.560
I prefer Dark Matter coffee.

24:37.643 --> 24:39.312
There's one about twelve blocks from here.

24:39.395 --> 24:42.190
Why don't you go get me a red eye
and get yourself whatever you want.

24:42.273 --> 24:43.524
Thanks. I'll be back in a jiff.

24:45.526 --> 24:46.527
(SIGHS)

24:50.031 --> 24:52.909
Hey, uh, Keisha's father,
Darrell, arrived.

24:52.992 --> 24:54.535
Had a lot of questions.

24:54.619 --> 24:56.746
I know. I need to go talk to them.

24:56.829 --> 24:59.415
I'm not avoiding them.
I just don't have the answers yet.

25:00.249 --> 25:03.502
What'd her CT show?
Came back negative. No bleed.

25:03.586 --> 25:05.004
Bloodwork?

25:05.087 --> 25:08.382
Glucose and sodium are a little low,
but otherwise normal.

25:09.091 --> 25:10.551
I'm gonna do an LP,
make sure we're not looking

25:10.635 --> 25:11.928
at something like meningitis.

25:12.762 --> 25:15.389
Are you sure that's necessary?
Is she spiking a fever?

25:15.473 --> 25:18.017
Well, not today, but her mom said
she was last week,

25:18.100 --> 25:19.727
so, I gotta check it off my list.

25:19.810 --> 25:21.854
Hey, you want me
to take over Keisha for you?

25:21.938 --> 25:23.856
What? Why?

25:23.940 --> 25:26.150
It's... Nat, it's been a long week.

25:26.234 --> 25:27.693
You know, and you were
out of action for a while.

25:27.777 --> 25:30.029
I'd understand if you're
feeling a little rusty.

25:30.112 --> 25:32.240
Maybe you should look into that program
I mentioned earlier...

25:32.323 --> 25:33.950
This is because I misspoke, isn't it?

25:35.660 --> 25:38.204
You are fixated
on me getting my memory back.

25:39.372 --> 25:40.373
Why?

25:41.499 --> 25:43.834
Nat, I just want you to get better.
Nah, I don't think that's it.

25:45.253 --> 25:46.295
I think it's about you.

25:47.630 --> 25:49.674
You want me to remember
why I came to see you that night,

25:50.675 --> 25:51.926
so that maybe I'll...

25:54.220 --> 25:55.763
...tell you something you wanna hear.

25:56.472 --> 25:57.848
Natalie, no...
Stop it.

25:59.684 --> 26:00.685
I am fine.

26:01.477 --> 26:02.770
And I don't appreciate you talking

26:02.853 --> 26:04.855
to Dr. Abrams about
my health behind my back.

26:05.815 --> 26:08.025
Monique. Will you prep Keisha for an LP?
MONIQUE: Okay.

26:08.109 --> 26:10.194
Thanks.
Actually, Monique, hold off on that.

26:11.862 --> 26:13.990
I didn't want to have to tell you this,
but I'm taking over the patient.

26:15.366 --> 26:16.951
The parents have lost confidence in you.

26:17.576 --> 26:19.078
They brought their daughter in
to have a burn looked at,

26:19.161 --> 26:20.162
and now she's in a coma.

26:20.246 --> 26:23.666
Will, please don't do this.

26:24.250 --> 26:26.752
I'm sorry, they want you off the case.

26:31.132 --> 26:32.133
(SIGHS)

26:33.092 --> 26:34.510
Juliette!

26:34.593 --> 26:37.346
Twentyâ€“threeâ€“yearâ€“old female,
found down, intubated in the field,

26:37.430 --> 26:39.223
18 gauge in the left arm.
She's eviscerated.

26:39.307 --> 26:41.934
Baghdad!
Bowels wrapped in moist saline gauze.

26:42.018 --> 26:43.519
She's gotten 500 mils of crystalloid.

26:43.602 --> 26:45.313
MAGGIE: Let's go, everybody.
Let's go, let's go!

26:48.274 --> 26:52.987
All right. On my count. One, two, three.

26:54.322 --> 26:55.323
Get her on the monitors.

26:57.408 --> 27:00.119
APRIL: Heart rate's 130. BP's 72 over 44.

27:00.202 --> 27:03.497
Trigger the MTP. Open the hybrid room.

27:03.581 --> 27:04.582
I got you.

27:05.458 --> 27:07.126
Open the hybrid.
Oh, man,

27:07.710 --> 27:09.712
her uterus is cut wide open.

27:10.963 --> 27:13.007
Looks like she was pregnant.
Wait, what? Where's the baby?

27:13.090 --> 27:15.217
Where's this woman's baby?
There was no baby onâ€“site.

27:15.801 --> 27:16.802
It had to have been Nicole.

27:16.886 --> 27:19.597
Okay. Okay, this woman who did this,
her name is Nicole Burke,

27:19.680 --> 27:21.223
she is in the NICU right now
with the baby.

27:21.307 --> 27:22.933
Come on, I'll show you.
Stop!

27:23.017 --> 27:25.353
Let the police do their job, Sexton!
Come here and help me retract.

27:25.436 --> 27:28.898
You have to go up there fast! Oh, my God.

27:28.981 --> 27:30.358
I need some more lab sponges.

27:30.441 --> 27:31.442
NURSE: Yes, Doctor.

27:37.323 --> 27:39.617
MARCEL: So, what do you think?
Can we save the uterus?

27:40.659 --> 27:43.079
I don't know. It's looking pretty ratty.

27:43.162 --> 27:44.246
Even if we can fix it,

27:44.330 --> 27:46.999
she'd run the risk of it rupturing
with a future pregnancy.

27:47.083 --> 27:48.292
I'd just do a hysterectomy.

27:49.543 --> 27:52.588
Well, she's only 23, and I'm not sure
her baby's gonna survive.

27:54.006 --> 27:55.007
I'm gonna try and save it.

27:55.633 --> 27:58.969
I'll go scrub, but for the record,
this is against my better judgment.

27:59.929 --> 28:03.099
You scrubbing in or not, Mags?
I'm coming!

28:04.141 --> 28:06.852
Oh, uh... Hey, Maggie, are you all right?

28:06.936 --> 28:08.020
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

28:08.104 --> 28:10.773
Should I jump in? I'm... I'm certified.

28:11.690 --> 28:12.691
I'm fine.

28:18.280 --> 28:19.657
Why does this keep happening?

28:20.533 --> 28:23.285
The drugs he took
are making his heart stop

28:23.369 --> 28:25.162
and until they clear his system...

28:27.081 --> 28:28.958
(CRYING)

28:35.923 --> 28:39.176
Feels like only yesterday we were waiting

28:39.260 --> 28:41.762
to see what college
he would get into and...

28:41.846 --> 28:42.847
Now?

28:44.557 --> 28:46.976
We just couldn't let him go through
with that plan of his, you know?

28:49.103 --> 28:50.563
The...

28:50.646 --> 28:55.526
The thought of his head just floating
in a canister in a warehouse somewhere...

28:58.237 --> 29:00.948
Shep told me that he tried to talk
to you two about this, is that right?

29:01.031 --> 29:02.032
Yeah.

29:03.117 --> 29:04.118
I don't know if it's any comfort,

29:04.201 --> 29:07.663
but I was genuinely impressed

29:07.746 --> 29:09.248
with how much thought
that he had put into this,

29:09.331 --> 29:11.125
and how much sense that it made to him.

29:12.918 --> 29:16.547
Please, Dr. Charles,
tell us what we're missing.

29:19.675 --> 29:21.135
Miss Shepard, I've been
doing this for a while.

29:22.052 --> 29:23.596
And on a good day,

29:23.679 --> 29:27.558
I'm just starting to think I might be
learning my way around the human mind.

29:29.101 --> 29:30.102
But trying to...

29:30.186 --> 29:33.022
To fathom the thinking of someone
who's confronting their own mortality?

29:34.106 --> 29:35.566
Unless you're the one who's looking down
that tunnel,

29:35.649 --> 29:37.234
I just... I don't know if it's possible.

29:39.445 --> 29:41.197
I think what we need to do
is try and listen,

29:42.114 --> 29:45.034
understand and respect
that it's their journey

29:45.117 --> 29:46.452
to... To go on alone.

29:47.620 --> 29:51.624
They got his heart back in rhythm.
You should go be with him.

29:58.005 --> 30:00.049
What we need to do?

30:02.468 --> 30:06.764
You give us the power to make a decision
and then judge us for making it?

30:07.765 --> 30:09.808
Mr. Shepard, believe me,
I'm... I'm not judging anybody.

30:17.024 --> 30:18.651
Anyone from rheumatology showed up yet?

30:18.734 --> 30:19.735
No.

30:19.818 --> 30:22.196
Lean on them, okay?
And run another set of labs.

30:22.279 --> 30:23.697
MONIQUE: Mmmâ€“hmm.

30:23.781 --> 30:25.407
Oh, hey, there. Again.

30:27.159 --> 30:28.827
Hi, Owen.
Hi, Will.

30:29.662 --> 30:32.039
PHILLIP: After we got done in the park,

30:32.122 --> 30:33.874
we went to the movies,

30:33.958 --> 30:36.919
and then we figured we would
come here and wait for Mommy.

30:39.046 --> 30:40.297
Hey, Phillip...

30:40.381 --> 30:41.382
Yeah?

30:44.260 --> 30:46.804
Not so sure this is the best place
for kids, you know?

30:47.763 --> 30:50.432
Some scary stuff happens here,
and maybe they can't unsee.

30:50.516 --> 30:52.393
Oh, yeah. That's a good point.

30:53.352 --> 30:54.353
Um...

30:59.525 --> 31:03.737
There we go. Now there's nothing
to unsee, right?

31:14.081 --> 31:16.500
We told your supervisor we didn't want you
treating our daughter anymore...

31:16.584 --> 31:17.585
I know, I just need

31:17.668 --> 31:19.211
to check one last thing.
Dr. Manning?

31:20.462 --> 31:22.047
I'll have to ask you to stay away
from this patient.

31:22.673 --> 31:23.841
I was wrong. Okay?

31:23.924 --> 31:26.343
Etomidate and ketamine
are not just the same thing.

31:26.427 --> 31:30.931
A big difference is that etomidate
unmasks adrenal insufficiencies...

31:31.015 --> 31:32.099
While ketamine doesn't.

31:32.182 --> 31:33.183
Yes.

31:34.935 --> 31:36.812
Do you see the pigment spots
on Keisha's foot?

31:37.813 --> 31:41.859
They are a sign that her adrenal glands
are not producing enough cortisol.

31:41.942 --> 31:44.570
100 milligrams of hydrocortisone.
I don't understand.

31:44.653 --> 31:46.488
Cortisol helps the body handle stress.

31:46.572 --> 31:49.199
In its absence, even the stress
of being examined by a doctor

31:49.283 --> 31:51.285
was enough to plummet Keisha into a coma.

31:54.538 --> 31:56.332
(MACHINE BEEPS)

31:56.415 --> 31:57.416
BP's improving.

31:59.126 --> 32:00.419
Her color's coming back.

32:00.502 --> 32:02.129
She's trying to open her eyes!

32:02.212 --> 32:03.547
Oh, my baby girl...

32:08.719 --> 32:09.928
She's superâ€“cold.

32:10.012 --> 32:11.388
I'm having trouble
keeping her pressure up.

32:11.472 --> 32:12.640
You need to pack her up now and get out.

32:13.307 --> 32:15.976
Told you it wasn't worth it.
Knot and I'm done.

32:16.060 --> 32:17.394
You're pushing it, Dr. Marcel.

32:17.478 --> 32:20.147
And there. Done.

32:21.607 --> 32:24.610
Looks better than I thought.
Let's tempâ€“close and get her upstairs.

32:24.693 --> 32:25.861
Open up a vac sponge.

32:25.944 --> 32:27.613
(BREATHING HEAVILY)
Maggie?

32:28.822 --> 32:29.823
I need to take a minute.

32:33.952 --> 32:34.953
MARCEL: Mags.

32:37.956 --> 32:39.958
Sexton, scrub in!

32:42.294 --> 32:44.630
(SOBBING)

32:44.713 --> 32:50.427
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

32:50.511 --> 32:51.845
Hey.

32:51.929 --> 32:55.683
If you need to go home early,
I'm more than willing to cover for you.

33:00.646 --> 33:01.897
You cover for me?

33:03.691 --> 33:04.817
Your first day?

33:06.568 --> 33:10.322
(LAUGHING)

33:11.782 --> 33:13.867
A little constructive criticism, Paula,

33:16.370 --> 33:20.249
you have an insanely inflated sense
of your own capabilities.

33:22.251 --> 33:25.587
"You know, I'm certified doing this.
I did my dissertation on that."

33:26.338 --> 33:27.548
Please!

33:28.549 --> 33:29.633
I'm...
Get out.

33:33.387 --> 33:35.848
I'm sorry, but I refuse
to be spoken to like that.

33:36.932 --> 33:39.643
(SOBBING)

33:56.785 --> 33:57.786
Is she gonna make it?

33:58.787 --> 34:02.416
Yeah, she lost a lot of blood,
but, yeah, I'm hopeful.

34:02.499 --> 34:04.710
Do we know any more about what happened?

34:05.461 --> 34:07.045
The victim's name is Louisa Nash.

34:07.129 --> 34:09.006
She and the assailant were coâ€“workers.

34:09.089 --> 34:11.008
This morning,
Miss Burke invited Louisa over

34:11.091 --> 34:12.718
to give her some old baby clothes.

34:12.801 --> 34:14.178
When her guard was down,
she chloroformed her

34:14.261 --> 34:17.765
and forcibly removed the baby.
Who would ever do something like that?

34:18.640 --> 34:20.517
She lost her son recently to leukemia.

34:20.601 --> 34:22.936
Maybe she had some sort of
mental breakdown? I don't know.

34:24.313 --> 34:26.732
We were lucky and we got an anonymous tip
about Miss Burke.

34:26.815 --> 34:28.692
And that helped us find Louisa in time.

34:28.776 --> 34:30.319
Suspect's hand needs dressing.

34:30.402 --> 34:32.404
Is that something you can do here?
I got it.

34:41.079 --> 34:42.873
Take care of my baby, okay?

34:45.042 --> 34:47.044
Tell him I'll come for him
as soon as I can.

34:51.048 --> 34:52.966
It's getting to be a bit of a circus.

34:54.426 --> 34:55.427
Gwen? Gwen?
Excuse me?

34:55.511 --> 34:57.012
Here. I'll take you out the back way.

35:13.821 --> 35:16.532
What's going on?
They're withdrawing support.

35:18.951 --> 35:21.578
My wife and I decided we're going to honor
our son's wishes.

35:23.413 --> 35:26.333
This way, maybe, someday,
we'll get our son back.

35:29.336 --> 35:31.672
(FLATLINING)

35:32.589 --> 35:33.882
Time of death, 19:42.

36:07.541 --> 36:09.960
So, I'm thinking
this might have been precipitated

36:10.043 --> 36:11.879
by some kind of underlying cause.

36:11.962 --> 36:15.340
Maybe Addison's Disease? I'm gonna
have endocrinology come down and see her.

36:17.092 --> 36:18.802
I thought it was clear
I was gonna be the primary.

36:19.553 --> 36:21.930
I'm sorry, but once I realized
what caused her to crash,

36:22.014 --> 36:24.516
I had to act quickly.
I mean, Keisha could have died.

36:25.976 --> 36:27.436
Oh, my ride's here.

36:30.647 --> 36:33.942
Adrenal crisis should have been
on your differential from the start.

36:35.152 --> 36:36.528
It was an odd presentation.

36:37.571 --> 36:38.906
Or you just weren't thinking straight.

36:41.325 --> 36:43.243
I'm gonna want to oversee
all your cases moving forward,

36:43.327 --> 36:46.914
until we know for sure your TBI
isn't adversely affecting your patients.

36:46.997 --> 36:50.626
Are you serious?
There's nothing wrong with me.

36:51.752 --> 36:53.337
You don't have the authority.

36:54.838 --> 36:56.214
I was hoping we could do this offâ€“book.

36:58.425 --> 37:00.886
If not, we can formalize it
with Lanik and Goodwin.

37:00.969 --> 37:01.970
I'm happy to talk to them.

37:04.723 --> 37:05.724
Natalie,

37:07.559 --> 37:08.560
it's for your own protection.

37:10.604 --> 37:13.106
Why do I feel like you're punishing me
for something else?

37:22.491 --> 37:24.785
Hi, come here. (GRUNTS)

37:26.119 --> 37:27.621
So, you ready to go?
PHILLIP: Yeah.

37:28.705 --> 37:29.706
Yes.

37:36.838 --> 37:39.591
Louisa? Can you open your eyes for me?

37:43.553 --> 37:44.554
Hey.

37:44.638 --> 37:48.308
You're at Gaffney Chicago
Medical Center, in the ICU.

37:48.392 --> 37:50.185
You sustained some injuries
that required us

37:50.268 --> 37:53.230
to perform extensive surgery,
but you are okay.

37:54.690 --> 37:56.233
Would you like to meet your baby girl?

37:57.275 --> 37:58.652
Uhâ€“huh.

38:07.077 --> 38:08.245
Here she is.

38:15.961 --> 38:18.797
We got lucky, the police
finding her in time.

38:21.049 --> 38:22.509
Can I trust you to keep a secret?

38:23.552 --> 38:24.720
Yeah. What?

38:27.848 --> 38:30.308
You know how that monster was so antsy
to get out of here earlier?

38:30.392 --> 38:31.393
Mmmâ€“hmm.

38:31.476 --> 38:33.520
Well, Dr. Marcel gave her enough Ativan

38:33.603 --> 38:36.064
to knock her out, and while she was,

38:36.148 --> 38:38.817
he drew some blood
and had her HCG levels checked

38:38.900 --> 38:41.319
to see if she really delivered that baby.

38:41.403 --> 38:43.488
What?
You can't tell anyone, April.

38:43.572 --> 38:44.823
Crockett could get fired.

38:45.949 --> 38:47.242
He's such a badass.

38:48.076 --> 38:49.161
Do you know if he's seeing anybody?

38:50.579 --> 38:51.580
No, I don't.

38:56.793 --> 38:57.919
Paula quit?

38:58.003 --> 39:00.589
Yeah. She said, and I quote,

39:00.672 --> 39:03.008
"the ED wasn't a healthy environment"
for her.

39:03.091 --> 39:04.968
You know, I had a feeling
that she couldn't cut it.

39:05.052 --> 39:08.013
You chased her off, Maggie.
And I told you

39:08.096 --> 39:10.140
that I don't need the help.

39:10.223 --> 39:11.308
You're being stubborn.

39:12.559 --> 39:13.894
I have a hospital to run.

39:14.561 --> 39:17.189
So, if you don't want us
to treat you medically,

39:17.898 --> 39:19.066
then you're getting help.

39:20.525 --> 39:22.194
(RUSTLING)

39:27.115 --> 39:28.533
April?
Yeah.

39:29.993 --> 39:32.287
Thank you for scrubbing in for me today.
Yeah.

39:33.455 --> 39:37.834
I'd like to start training you
to take over the position formally.

39:39.669 --> 39:40.670
Sure, of course.

39:41.797 --> 39:43.381
It'll help me take some stuff
off my plate.

39:45.342 --> 39:48.095
Does that mean I'd be working
with Dr. Marcel?

39:48.178 --> 39:49.179
Is that a problem?

39:50.388 --> 39:51.389
No.

39:52.641 --> 39:53.642
Start tomorrow?

39:54.518 --> 39:55.560
Okay.

39:55.644 --> 39:56.645
Thank you.

39:59.064 --> 40:00.065
Thank you.

40:02.484 --> 40:04.736
Do you really think I'll get better care
here than at East Mercy?

40:05.654 --> 40:06.655
Yeah.

40:16.748 --> 40:17.749
CAROLINE: Hey.

40:18.750 --> 40:20.210
Why didn't you wait for me?

40:20.293 --> 40:22.587
Because you were still on rounds.

40:22.671 --> 40:24.381
And Sharon offered me a ride home.

40:26.967 --> 40:27.968
How did your, um...

40:29.594 --> 40:30.595
How'd your surgery go?

40:31.429 --> 40:32.430
I didn't get it.

40:35.767 --> 40:37.602
You didn't?
No.

40:37.686 --> 40:41.314
They're gonna check my wrist again
in four weeks

40:41.398 --> 40:42.732
to see if I still need a cast.

40:46.027 --> 40:48.029
(KETTLE WHISTLING)

40:57.831 --> 40:58.832
Let me get that for you.

41:00.167 --> 41:01.168
(POURING WATER)

41:07.799 --> 41:09.926
You best not mess up my Baked Alaska.

41:12.721 --> 41:13.722
No, ma'am.

41:24.774 --> 41:26.776
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
